WEBVTT

00:03.465 --> 00:06.137
<i>[beetles buzzing]</i>

00:06.137 --> 00:09.352
[thunder rumbling]

00:09.352 --> 00:12.358
[beetles continue buzzing]

00:15.405 --> 00:18.411
[thunder rumbling]

00:18.411 --> 00:21.417
‐ [breathing heavily]

00:28.431 --> 00:32.524
[water splashing,
Annie panting]

00:32.524 --> 00:34.318
[switch clicks]

00:41.040 --> 00:44.005
<i>[ominous ambient music]</i>

00:44.005 --> 00:47.011
[thunder rumbles loudly]

00:54.901 --> 00:57.949
[breathing rapidly]

00:57.949 --> 01:04.963
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16.695 --> 01:19.701
<i>[music heightens]</i>

01:19.701 --> 01:26.674
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:34.773 --> 01:37.779
<i>[thunder crashes]</i>

01:44.960 --> 01:47.632
[insects chirping]

01:47.632 --> 01:50.345
<i>[ominous, grinding music]</i>

01:50.345 --> 01:52.809
[dirt and roots rustling]

01:52.809 --> 01:55.815
[Annie panting]

02:00.658 --> 02:07.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:11.597 --> 02:14.059
[grunting]

02:14.059 --> 02:19.069
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:19.069 --> 02:21.867
[Annie gasps,
flashlight clatters]

02:21.867 --> 02:23.913
[flashlight clatters,
water splashes]

02:23.913 --> 02:26.835
[panting]

02:26.835 --> 02:28.338
[wood groans]

02:28.338 --> 02:29.465
[yelps]

02:30.635 --> 02:33.139
[panting]

02:33.139 --> 02:36.145
[thunder rumbling,
rain dripping]

02:36.145 --> 02:41.740
[wheezing]

02:51.677 --> 02:54.808
[whimpers]

02:54.808 --> 02:57.814
<i>[tense music]</i>

02:57.814 --> 03:04.828
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:29.628 --> 03:31.840
[rocks clattering,
Annie panting]

03:34.303 --> 03:37.309
<i>[music darkens]</i>

03:37.309 --> 03:43.739
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:43.739 --> 03:45.910
[thunder rumbles]

03:45.910 --> 03:52.757
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:52.757 --> 03:55.136
[metal clanks]

04:01.858 --> 04:04.864
[water running]

04:10.417 --> 04:12.379
[water splashes]

04:17.222 --> 04:24.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:41.020 --> 04:44.026
<i>[music quickening rapidly]</i>

04:44.026 --> 04:50.915
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:50.915 --> 04:53.294
<i>[music echoes, fades]</i>

04:57.804 --> 05:00.391
Wha...what on Earth?

05:04.734 --> 05:06.696
[footsteps pounding overhead]

05:28.030 --> 05:30.201
[wood creaks overhead]

05:30.201 --> 05:34.627
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:34.627 --> 05:36.005
[wood clatters]

05:38.092 --> 05:43.311
[panting]

05:50.826 --> 05:57.840
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:00.303 --> 06:03.309
[faint pounding]

06:11.408 --> 06:14.414
[Annie gasps,
rocking horse clatters]

06:14.414 --> 06:21.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:31.658 --> 06:33.327
[faint pounding continues]

06:33.327 --> 06:34.622
[distant grunting]

06:37.586 --> 06:40.592
[grunting and pounding
continues]

06:50.738 --> 06:52.658
‐ [shrieks]
ANNIE: Christmas!

06:52.658 --> 06:55.664
<i>[sinister music]</i>

06:55.664 --> 07:02.052
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:02.052 --> 07:05.058
[thunder rumbling]

07:10.151 --> 07:13.157
<i>[music building]</i>

07:13.157 --> 07:19.796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:19.796 --> 07:22.885
<i>[ominous music]</i>

07:22.885 --> 07:29.899
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:51.985 --> 07:54.991
[waves crashing,
helicopter whirring]

07:56.619 --> 07:59.625
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:59.625 --> 08:02.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:02.756 --> 08:05.804
<i>[radio chatter]</i>

08:05.804 --> 08:12.818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:15.489 --> 08:18.622
<i>[music booms and fades]</i>

08:18.622 --> 08:21.376
[wheels rumbling]

08:35.781 --> 08:37.785
[equipment rustling]

08:45.509 --> 08:48.515
<i>[eerie ambient music]</i>

08:48.515 --> 08:51.103
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:51.103 --> 08:54.109
[pages rustling]

08:54.109 --> 09:01.123
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:10.851 --> 09:13.898
[engine idling]

09:17.531 --> 09:19.785
[key clicks, engine silences]

09:21.288 --> 09:23.960
[rain pattering]

09:23.960 --> 09:27.050
<i>[ominous, grinding music]</i>

09:27.050 --> 09:34.022
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:39.909 --> 09:43.248
<i>[music booms and fades]</i>

09:48.467 --> 09:53.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:53.102 --> 09:56.651
No. No, no, no, no, no.

09:56.651 --> 10:03.665
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:03.665 --> 10:06.336
[car door slams]

10:06.336 --> 10:10.679
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:10.679 --> 10:12.306
[latch clicks]

10:12.306 --> 10:14.436
JOY: Mom!
[door slams]

10:14.436 --> 10:16.566
Are you okay?

10:16.566 --> 10:19.739
Oh, my God, what happened?

10:19.739 --> 10:21.784
‐ Have you seen my necklace?

10:22.828 --> 10:24.582
‐ What? No.

10:27.921 --> 10:29.842
Were you in another accident?

10:29.842 --> 10:31.888
M‐‐Mom, you're all bloody.

10:31.888 --> 10:35.394
ANNIE: Things have changed.
We can't stay here.

10:35.394 --> 10:36.647
‐ What?

10:36.647 --> 10:39.319
Mom, slow down a moment.
What happened?

10:39.319 --> 10:41.031
You sa‐‐you said
we could stay here.

10:41.031 --> 10:43.202
ANNIE: I know, little love,
but this place...

10:43.202 --> 10:46.500
‐ It isn't the Laughing Place.
I know.

10:46.500 --> 10:48.086
‐ No.

10:48.086 --> 10:51.719
‐ But Mom, please.
I like it here.

10:51.719 --> 10:54.307
ANNIE: Joy, I cannot,
in good conscience,

10:54.307 --> 10:56.771
allow my daughter
to stay in a place like this.

10:56.771 --> 10:58.106
JOY: You promised!

10:58.106 --> 11:01.238
You can't just go back
on your promise like that.

11:01.238 --> 11:03.492
‐ Joy.

11:03.492 --> 11:06.289
You listen to me, now.

11:06.289 --> 11:10.256
When the person
who loves you most and best

11:10.256 --> 11:13.888
in this filthy world
asks you to trust them,

11:13.888 --> 11:16.351
then you listen
to that person, Joy,

11:16.351 --> 11:20.109
because that person
has fought for you

11:20.109 --> 11:24.117
and that person knows
what danger is, Joy,

11:24.117 --> 11:25.912
in a way that you don't!

11:25.912 --> 11:29.419
[lock clicks]
And I pray that you never will!

11:29.419 --> 11:33.176
‐ [panting softly]
‐ Joy!

11:33.176 --> 11:35.599
Joy!

11:35.599 --> 11:42.613
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:43.196 --> 11:47.496
<i>ANNOUNCER ON TV:</i>
<i>...and the crowd is loving it.</i>

11:47.496 --> 11:49.042
<i>It's the bottom of...</i>

11:55.471 --> 11:57.308
NADIA: I got this, Julie.
‐ Thanks, Dr. H.

11:57.308 --> 12:00.189
NADIA: No problem.

12:06.242 --> 12:08.038
‐ Oh, hello.

12:08.038 --> 12:10.752
‐ Hi. [kisses]

12:10.752 --> 12:12.923
‐ What are you doing here?

12:12.923 --> 12:15.094
You gonna
give me my poison today?

12:17.139 --> 12:20.104
Hey. Hey, hey. What's wrong?

12:23.026 --> 12:25.532
‐ It's Ace.

12:25.532 --> 12:27.703
‐ What's up?

12:27.703 --> 12:30.959
‐ He threw a Molotov cocktail
through the window
of our house.

12:30.959 --> 12:33.631
<i>ANNOUNCER ON TV:</i>
<i>It's a hard hit!</i>

12:33.631 --> 12:35.677
POP: ...fuckin' kill him.
NADIA: Pop!

12:35.677 --> 12:37.514
Pop. No, wait. Listen to me.

12:37.514 --> 12:40.102
‐ Is Abdi okay?
NADIA: He's fine.

12:40.102 --> 12:41.647
Sit down.
We gotta talk about this.

12:41.647 --> 12:42.649
‐ What's Abdi gonna do?

12:42.649 --> 12:44.737
‐ Honestly?
I don't know.

12:44.737 --> 12:46.657
POP: Tell Abdi
to fucking sit tight.

12:46.657 --> 12:49.997
It's for me to sort out.
My mess to clean up.

12:49.997 --> 12:53.086
Tell Abdi,
"Lay low. Do nothing."

12:53.086 --> 12:55.550
[door slams]

12:55.550 --> 12:58.681
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

12:58.681 --> 13:00.977
[keys jingle, latch clicks]

13:00.977 --> 13:03.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:03.900 --> 13:05.444
ABDI: [sighs]

13:05.444 --> 13:06.822
[gun magazine clicks]

13:06.822 --> 13:13.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:17.301 --> 13:18.971
[car doors slam]

13:18.971 --> 13:25.985
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:28.031 --> 13:29.910
[pounding on door]
CHRIS: Hey, dipshit.

13:29.910 --> 13:31.914
[pounding continues]

13:34.210 --> 13:37.717
You'd better be sick or dead.
I shit you not.

13:37.717 --> 13:39.680
Hey, asshole.

13:39.680 --> 13:40.890
Hey, you were supposed
to meet me at‐‐

13:40.890 --> 13:43.896
[dog barking, whining]

13:45.482 --> 13:46.902
Jesus.

13:46.902 --> 13:48.238
[barking continues]

13:48.238 --> 13:49.240
Bobby, come here.

13:49.240 --> 13:51.160
Come here.

13:53.541 --> 13:56.254
[dog whining]

13:57.256 --> 14:00.262
[cell phone buzzing]

14:04.688 --> 14:07.694
[buzzing continues]

14:14.332 --> 14:16.503
Pop.
POP: Chris?

14:16.503 --> 14:18.423
<i>CHRIS: Yeah, it's me.</i>

14:18.423 --> 14:20.010
POP: The fuck?
What‐‐what's going on?

14:20.010 --> 14:21.137
Where the fuck is Ace?

14:21.137 --> 14:23.308
‐ No clue. Not here.

14:23.308 --> 14:26.147
He didn't feed Bobby Orr.
He was supposed to meet me
at the Bonsaint's.

14:26.147 --> 14:29.028
‐ Wait. That fuckwit
left his phone at home?

14:29.028 --> 14:31.407
<i>CHRIS: Yeah.</i>
‐ H'bout the truck?

14:31.407 --> 14:33.244
<i>CHRIS: It's still here.</i>

14:33.244 --> 14:35.415
[car door clatters]
‐ Call me if you see him.

14:37.629 --> 14:40.635
[dog lapping water]

14:42.262 --> 14:48.400
‐ Come here, Bobby.

14:48.400 --> 14:50.780
[dog whines]
I know, babe.

14:50.780 --> 14:53.661
Hang on. Hang on.

14:53.661 --> 14:55.372
Hang on.
[dog barks, growls]

14:55.372 --> 14:56.583
Hang on, Bobby.
[dog barks]

14:56.583 --> 14:58.420
Bobby. Bobby.
[dog barking, growling]

14:58.420 --> 15:00.382
<i>JOY: You always do this,</i>
<i>and I'm tired of it!</i>

15:00.382 --> 15:04.098
[barking continues]
<i>ANNIE: Joy, I told you to pack</i>
<i>up your stuff right now!</i>

15:04.098 --> 15:06.060
<i>JOY: I'm not going anywhere.</i>

15:07.897 --> 15:09.568
ANNIE: Get back here,
little lady!

15:09.568 --> 15:11.195
‐ [grunts]

15:11.195 --> 15:12.741
‐ Where do you think
you're going?

15:12.741 --> 15:14.076
‐ I'm going
to my friend's house.

15:14.076 --> 15:16.540
‐ Oh, no, you're not!

15:16.540 --> 15:19.211
‐ Sorry, Ms. Ingalls. She's...

15:19.211 --> 15:22.134
‐ Joy!
‐ I'm not leaving!

15:22.134 --> 15:24.514
[shouts, gasps]

15:24.514 --> 15:26.267
[flesh squelches,
Joy pants]

15:31.402 --> 15:34.408
[church bell tolling]

15:35.745 --> 15:39.503
<i>PASTOR:</i>
<i>The Army went to Somalia</i>
<i>to help feed the hungry,</i>

15:39.503 --> 15:42.299
to sweep away the bad guys
with the guns,

15:42.299 --> 15:43.761
to‐‐to free the people.

15:43.761 --> 15:46.975
But things don't always go
the way we hope, do they?

15:46.975 --> 15:48.729
For any of us.
TRANSLATOR: [speaking softly in Somali]

15:48.729 --> 15:50.398
PASTOR: And they sure didn't
over there.

15:50.398 --> 15:51.777
[translator continues softly]

15:51.777 --> 15:57.079
So all we can do now
is to extend a hand...

15:57.079 --> 15:59.543
in both directions.

15:59.543 --> 16:01.254
Remember Romans:

16:01.254 --> 16:04.845
"We are all
each other's brothers."

16:04.845 --> 16:08.936
Well, no one here
has been more of a brother

16:08.936 --> 16:11.315
than Pop Merrill.

16:11.315 --> 16:13.988
When he found out
what happened in your country,

16:13.988 --> 16:18.204
he insisted we help find you
a new home here in Maine.

16:18.204 --> 16:21.043
And today,
I am happy to announce

16:21.043 --> 16:24.300
Pop's offered spaces
in his warehouse on Pine

16:24.300 --> 16:27.724
to any refugees looking
to open their own business.

16:27.724 --> 16:28.976
Pop.

16:28.976 --> 16:31.982
[applause]

16:32.984 --> 16:35.990
<i>[melancholy, tense music]</i>

16:35.990 --> 16:42.962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:49.350 --> 16:51.855
[door clunks, slams]

16:51.855 --> 16:58.869
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:00.038 --> 17:04.421
CITIZEN: [angrily] You spent
most of the budget on those
ugly‐ass witch scarecrows

17:04.421 --> 17:06.300
that caused
that damn car crash.

17:06.300 --> 17:08.555
Now you want us to give more
for a parade?

17:08.555 --> 17:11.770
PINTO: To celebrate
the original founders
of this town.

17:11.770 --> 17:15.903
You all elected a new council
to bring Castle Rock
back to life.

17:15.903 --> 17:19.076
‐ You ran unopposed.
BAR MANAGER: Pop.

17:19.076 --> 17:22.082
<i>[mellow, jazzy music playing</i>
<i>over speakers]</i>

17:22.082 --> 17:26.090
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:26.090 --> 17:28.637
PINTO: Okay, um, this town has
as much history...

17:28.637 --> 17:30.933
‐ Ace been around?
[Pinto continues indistinctly]

17:30.933 --> 17:33.438
‐ A few days ago, maybe.
PINTO: Sure, we've had
our dark moments.

17:33.438 --> 17:35.066
But who hasn't?

17:35.066 --> 17:38.406
We can use our past
to help get started
on our future.

17:38.406 --> 17:41.245
For example,
do you all have any idea

17:41.245 --> 17:45.211
what kind of Boston dollars
Salem, Mass pulls in
from all the witch groupies?

17:45.211 --> 17:48.636
We had our own witches right
here in Castle Rock, people.

17:48.636 --> 17:50.848
‐ They were Satanists,

17:50.848 --> 17:53.019
not witches.

17:53.019 --> 17:55.983
Made a bad deal with
the wrong <i>hombre,</i> those folks,

17:55.983 --> 17:59.783
and they burned for it.

17:59.783 --> 18:03.206
We've been making bad deals
with the wrong fella
for a long, long time.

18:06.505 --> 18:09.594
‐ Pop, you okay?

18:12.474 --> 18:16.357
POP: Call me if you see Ace.

18:16.357 --> 18:19.196
<i>[K'naan's "America" playing]</i>

18:19.196 --> 18:22.202
K'NAAN:
[rapping in Somali]

18:22.202 --> 18:25.835
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:25.835 --> 18:27.964
LANCE:
Get the fuck out of my way.

18:27.964 --> 18:30.176
BILLY: Hey. You seen Ace?

18:30.176 --> 18:31.262
‐ [inaudible]
BOBBY: You ain't seen him?

18:31.262 --> 18:33.182
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:33.182 --> 18:35.061
BAR MANAGER: Here's my weekly.

18:35.061 --> 18:38.276
And, uh, as far as Ace goes,
he hasn't been around
in a few days.

18:38.276 --> 18:40.321
But if he comes this way,
I'll call you, Pop.

18:40.321 --> 18:44.622
K'NAAN: [rapping in Somali]

18:44.622 --> 18:46.125
LANCE: Get out of my way.

18:46.125 --> 18:47.754
BILLY: You seen Ace?
‐ No.

18:47.754 --> 18:50.091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:50.091 --> 18:52.805
LANCE: Where's Ace?
I know you seen him.

18:52.805 --> 18:54.893
‐ Either of you seen Ace?

18:54.893 --> 18:56.437
K'NAAN:
[rapping in Somali]

18:56.437 --> 18:58.609
JEANNIE:
You try the church, Pop?

18:58.609 --> 19:01.907
BILLY: He's M‐I‐fucking‐A.
Maybe even dead.

19:01.907 --> 19:04.453
Do you think anyone here
knows anything about that?

19:04.453 --> 19:06.792
‐ No. Why would they?

19:06.792 --> 19:09.087
K'NAAN:
♪ Certain things fresh
and certain things mish ♪

19:09.087 --> 19:11.718
♪ I got my own sound,
I don't sound like the rest ♪

19:11.718 --> 19:14.014
♪ And not long ago
I don't spoke English ♪

19:14.014 --> 19:16.520
♪ My point is police pull me
over a lot ♪

19:16.520 --> 19:19.107
♪ They wonder what kind
of rap sheet I got ♪

19:19.107 --> 19:21.487
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:21.487 --> 19:22.782
‐ Yeah, rake?

19:22.782 --> 19:25.538
‐ It's time to go.

19:25.538 --> 19:32.510
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:36.392 --> 19:37.435
[cell phone chirps]

19:37.435 --> 19:39.273
NADIA: Anne?

19:39.273 --> 19:42.655
What happened?
‐ Dr. H, this is Joy.

19:42.655 --> 19:44.826
‐ Hi.
NADIA: Hi, Joy. I'm Nadia.

19:44.826 --> 19:46.370
What happened here?

19:46.370 --> 19:47.582
ANNIE: It's a reinjury.

19:47.582 --> 19:48.917
‐ Burst stitches and shredding.

19:48.917 --> 19:50.336
‐ And she needs
a tetanus booster.

19:50.336 --> 19:51.380
It's been a few years.
‐ Okay.

19:51.380 --> 19:52.842
‐ It frickin' hurts.

19:52.842 --> 19:55.305
NADIA: Go ahead
and get her prepped.
‐ I will.

19:55.305 --> 19:56.725
‐ Appreciate it, Doc.

19:56.725 --> 19:59.564
JOY: I‐‐I don't need you
in there.

19:59.564 --> 20:01.233
‐ But I wanna come, love.

20:01.233 --> 20:04.448
‐ Stay in the waiting room.

20:04.448 --> 20:06.870
‐ She's 16, right?

20:06.870 --> 20:09.207
So technically, she can ask
for her privacy.

20:09.207 --> 20:11.170
‐ No, I think‐‐
NADIA: Don't worry.

20:11.170 --> 20:13.174
I'll take care of her.

20:13.174 --> 20:16.180
<i>[sinister, unhinged music]</i>

20:16.180 --> 20:23.194
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:25.616 --> 20:27.410
We got this.

20:31.628 --> 20:33.632
‐ I feel weird.

20:33.632 --> 20:35.301
NADIA: It's the anesthetic.

20:35.301 --> 20:38.558
Have you ever had
pain medicine like...

20:38.558 --> 20:39.644
at the dentist?

20:40.436 --> 20:41.523
‐ [sighs]

20:41.523 --> 20:43.527
My mom cleans my teeth.

20:43.527 --> 20:47.367
Her mom was a...
what's it called?

20:47.367 --> 20:49.664
A hygienist?

20:53.170 --> 20:55.551
‐ Who did these stitches, Joy?

20:58.347 --> 21:00.853
‐ My mom did them.

21:00.853 --> 21:02.773
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

21:02.773 --> 21:05.194
‐ Like, at home?

21:05.194 --> 21:11.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:11.290 --> 21:12.585
[pan clinks]

21:12.585 --> 21:16.300
So you and your mom,
you've moved around a lot?

21:16.300 --> 21:19.849
‐ Yeah.
Nurses have to, or else
they lose their license.

21:19.849 --> 21:23.355
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:23.355 --> 21:26.696
‐ Did your mom tell you that?

21:26.696 --> 21:33.710
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:34.252 --> 21:36.508
Joy?

21:36.508 --> 21:38.010
Just so you know,

21:38.010 --> 21:41.308
anything you tell me
is completely confidential.

21:41.308 --> 21:47.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:47.780 --> 21:50.953
‐ [exhales softly]

21:50.953 --> 21:53.959
[indistinct chatter]

21:53.959 --> 22:00.012
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:00.012 --> 22:02.392
‐ I want a fudge sundae.

22:02.392 --> 22:05.064
‐ [gagging]
‐ [grunting]

22:05.064 --> 22:07.152
[dog barking]

22:07.152 --> 22:08.822
<i>[pounding, tense music]</i>

22:08.822 --> 22:10.576
<i>ACE: [gagging]</i>
<i>[dog barking]</i>

22:10.576 --> 22:11.744
<i>ANNIE: [whimpers]</i>

22:11.744 --> 22:14.709
<i>[barking continues]</i>

22:14.709 --> 22:17.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:17.882 --> 22:19.342
<i>[music stutters, fades]</i>

22:19.342 --> 22:21.598
<i>[barking fades]</i>

22:21.598 --> 22:24.186
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:24.186 --> 22:31.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:31.200 --> 22:33.883
[indistinct chatter]

22:33.883 --> 22:36.108
<i>ABDI: [speaking Somali]</i>

23:00.884 --> 23:02.763
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:02.763 --> 23:04.892
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:04.892 --> 23:06.813
[keys jingle, car beeps]

23:11.686 --> 23:13.706
ABDI: Shh.
[speaks Somali]

23:15.464 --> 23:16.791
[indistinct conversation]

23:25.308 --> 23:27.186
ADMINISTRATOR:
Here's their IOM.

23:27.186 --> 23:28.355
[papers rustle]

23:28.355 --> 23:30.318
Lost their mom in the war.

23:30.318 --> 23:32.155
Managed to get here
by themselves.

23:34.660 --> 23:37.666
It's wonderful
what you're doing, Mr. Merrill.

23:37.666 --> 23:40.087
Fostering is such a gift.

23:40.087 --> 23:43.052
<i>[soft music]</i>

23:43.052 --> 23:50.066
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:52.188 --> 23:53.275
[Nadia and Abdi
speak Somali]

23:58.123 --> 24:01.129
[bag rustling]

24:05.429 --> 24:06.933
[cup taps]

24:06.933 --> 24:10.982
POP: It's called
"vanilla milkshake."

24:12.611 --> 24:14.907
No, no, no. Trust me. Try it.

24:14.907 --> 24:17.078
Trust me. It's good.

24:17.078 --> 24:19.625
Try.

24:22.214 --> 24:25.092
[Nadia and Abdi
speak Somali]

24:30.062 --> 24:32.442
POP: Wait a second.
Wait, whoa, whoa, whoa.

24:32.442 --> 24:35.907
You just told her she's not
gonna like it, didn't you?

24:35.907 --> 24:38.788
[both laughing]

24:38.788 --> 24:41.502
[both speaking Somali]
POP: [laughing]

24:41.502 --> 24:44.967
You got a future
in business, son. [laughs]

24:44.967 --> 24:46.679
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:46.679 --> 24:48.766
Ace. Chris. Get in here.

24:48.766 --> 24:51.104
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:51.104 --> 24:54.695
‐ Where's my fucking milkshake?

24:54.695 --> 24:56.364
<i>CHRIS: As soon as I find Ace,</i>

24:56.364 --> 24:58.620
I'm getting that piece of shit
put away this time.

24:58.620 --> 25:02.126
‐ Chris, just‐‐
‐ I'm serious. This is insane.

25:02.126 --> 25:03.963
‐ Pop's not gonna
get straight cops involved.

25:03.963 --> 25:06.176
His, maybe.
But you know the rules.

25:06.176 --> 25:09.432
‐ Well, fuck Pop's rules.
‐ Yeah?

25:14.568 --> 25:16.697
‐ Are you okay?

25:16.697 --> 25:18.785
‐ I guess.

25:20.120 --> 25:22.083
‐ [sighs]

25:22.083 --> 25:24.295
Did you get my message
the other night?

25:24.295 --> 25:26.049
Sorry about that.

25:26.049 --> 25:29.557
I had a few at the Tiger
and was just thinking...

25:29.557 --> 25:31.476
‐ Um, you know, with Abdi
and all this,

25:31.476 --> 25:35.484
I don't think
that it's a, uh, good idea.

25:35.484 --> 25:38.240
‐ No, no. Right.
Of course.

25:45.296 --> 25:47.884
Let me know
if Ace ends up in the ER.

25:47.884 --> 25:50.431
Or the morgue.

25:56.192 --> 25:58.280
[door closes]

25:58.280 --> 26:01.286
[heavy machinery clanking,
workers shouting commands]

26:12.643 --> 26:15.649
[machinery beeping]

26:15.649 --> 26:18.070
<i>[tense, strange music]</i>

26:18.070 --> 26:23.294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:23.294 --> 26:24.944
HASSAN:
[speaking Somali]

26:29.265 --> 26:30.736
WORKER:
[speaking Somali]

26:46.251 --> 26:48.756
‐ Go get them out.

26:48.756 --> 26:51.762
[heavy machinery clanking]

26:54.560 --> 26:56.897
<i>[echoing clank]</i>

27:05.205 --> 27:07.627
[distant engine rumbling]

27:11.134 --> 27:13.013
[door creaks]

27:13.013 --> 27:14.767
HASSAN: Security!

27:14.767 --> 27:18.148
Time to get the fuck out!

27:18.148 --> 27:21.822
<i>[ominous music]</i>

27:21.822 --> 27:25.162
I know you've been trespassing
in our land!

27:25.162 --> 27:32.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:36.100 --> 27:39.106
[food crackling]

27:39.106 --> 27:46.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:54.220 --> 27:55.723
Surprise, mo‐‐

27:55.723 --> 27:57.226
<i>[terrifying music]</i>

27:57.226 --> 27:59.063
What the fuck?

27:59.063 --> 28:02.444
[axe slicing,
skin squelching]

28:02.444 --> 28:04.616
[slicing continues]

28:09.668 --> 28:11.547
[door latch clanks]

28:11.547 --> 28:13.425
[door creaks open]

28:13.425 --> 28:15.345
[rhythmic, continuous thudding]

28:15.345 --> 28:18.351
<i>[sinister music]</i>

28:18.351 --> 28:25.032
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:25.032 --> 28:28.163
[ignition clicks off,
keys jingle]

28:29.708 --> 28:31.545
[car door slams]

28:31.545 --> 28:34.175
‐ Hear you were fucking with
my tenants at the mall, huh?

28:34.175 --> 28:36.220
‐ Just looking for Ace.
‐ Those are his tenants now.

28:36.220 --> 28:38.934
POP: Half of those folks been
in a shooting war‐‐a real one‐‐

28:38.934 --> 28:40.980
and every goddamn one
of those stalls

28:40.980 --> 28:43.151
at that bazaar
has got a gat
under the counter.

28:43.151 --> 28:45.030
You ready for war, tough guy?

28:45.030 --> 28:47.827
‐ Appreciate the advice,
but we don't work for you.

28:47.827 --> 28:50.207
‐ Cut it out now,

28:50.207 --> 28:53.338
before you fuck something
that can't be un‐fucked.

28:53.338 --> 28:54.758
BILLY:
Here's something fucked, Pop:

28:54.758 --> 28:57.764
over at Ace's mall, people say
Abdi's been shit‐talking.

28:57.764 --> 28:58.849
‐ About what?

28:58.849 --> 29:00.477
BILLY: Retaliation
for the fire.

29:00.477 --> 29:03.441
Killing your fucking nephew.

29:03.441 --> 29:06.280
POP: Fuckwits have no idea
what you're getting into.

29:06.280 --> 29:10.372
‐ Hey, feel better, Pop.
We're all pulling for you.

29:10.372 --> 29:13.378
[phone clicks, dials]

29:14.756 --> 29:16.635
<i>[line trilling]</i>

29:16.635 --> 29:19.140
<i>ABDI: This is Abdi.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

29:19.140 --> 29:20.935
‐ Abdi, it's me.

29:20.935 --> 29:25.611
I gotta talk to you.
It's important.

29:25.611 --> 29:27.239
[phone beeps, clicks shut]

29:28.283 --> 29:31.623
[dog barking]

29:34.086 --> 29:37.092
[dog barking]

29:40.307 --> 29:42.979
[barking, panting]

29:46.444 --> 29:49.450
<i>[suspicious music]</i>

29:49.450 --> 29:56.422
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:57.842 --> 29:58.844
[phone blips]

29:58.844 --> 30:02.894
‐ Search "nurse"
and "license"...

30:02.894 --> 30:06.234
and "job" and "term."

30:06.234 --> 30:07.612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:07.612 --> 30:09.533
<i>ACE: You're dripping.</i>

30:09.533 --> 30:11.620
[dog barking]

30:11.620 --> 30:16.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:16.588 --> 30:17.924
[phone blips]

30:17.924 --> 30:20.470
‐ Search "Anne Ingalls."

30:20.470 --> 30:25.940
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:25.940 --> 30:27.861
[phone blips]

30:27.861 --> 30:34.498
Search "Anne I‐N‐G‐A‐L‐L‐S,"

30:34.498 --> 30:36.127
end quote.

30:36.127 --> 30:42.389
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:46.648 --> 30:48.443
ANNIE: Where's my daughter?

30:48.443 --> 30:50.322
‐ We needed more space
for the blood drive.

30:50.322 --> 30:52.284
Dr. H moved her.
‐ Where?

30:52.284 --> 30:55.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:55.917 --> 30:58.631
POP: Ms. Ingalls?

30:58.631 --> 31:01.845
<i>[music stops abruptly]</i>

31:01.845 --> 31:03.807
You know my nephew.

31:03.807 --> 31:06.688
John? Ace?

31:06.688 --> 31:08.609
Manages the Stargazer.

31:09.485 --> 31:13.159
‐ Oh...no, I don't believe
I've ever m‐‐

31:13.159 --> 31:15.455
‐ Let's save some time
and cut through the bullshit.

31:15.455 --> 31:17.417
‐ [muttering quietly] Language.

31:17.417 --> 31:19.213
‐ He went to your cabin
last night.

31:21.885 --> 31:23.889
‐ I don't know
what you're insinuating‐‐

31:23.889 --> 31:26.310
POP: I'm not insinuating.
I'm telling.

31:26.310 --> 31:28.189
My nephew's missing.

31:28.189 --> 31:29.441
And his dog,

31:29.441 --> 31:32.072
who has considerably
better sense than him‐‐

31:32.072 --> 31:34.577
when I let him out
this afternoon,

31:34.577 --> 31:36.915
he went right to your door.

31:36.915 --> 31:39.044
Weird, right?

31:40.506 --> 31:43.261
But the thing
that confuses me most is...

31:43.261 --> 31:44.471
you're paid up
for another week,

31:44.471 --> 31:47.310
yet your bags are all packed.

31:47.310 --> 31:48.981
Hmm?

31:54.283 --> 31:56.955
‐ [sniffles]
He said he'd kill us.

31:56.955 --> 31:59.126
[breathing raggedly]

31:59.126 --> 32:01.840
He came to me. [sniffles]

32:01.840 --> 32:03.259
He had done something.

32:03.259 --> 32:05.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:05.598 --> 32:08.269
<i>[glass shattering]</i>

32:08.269 --> 32:09.981
Something about a fire...

32:09.981 --> 32:11.108
[glass shatters,
flames whoosh]

32:11.108 --> 32:12.862
<i>In Salem's Lot.</i>

32:12.862 --> 32:16.077
[fire alarm beeping]

32:16.077 --> 32:19.124
He said my daughter...

32:19.124 --> 32:21.212
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:21.212 --> 32:24.677
He said she'd seen something
that she shouldn't'a.

32:24.677 --> 32:26.723
But Joy hadn't seen
anything, I said.

32:26.723 --> 32:29.269
But he did not want
to take no...

32:29.269 --> 32:31.023
[breath hitches]

32:31.023 --> 32:35.031
He‐‐he seems like
the kind of man,
doesn't like to hear "no,"

32:35.031 --> 32:38.121
especially not from a woman.

32:38.121 --> 32:41.586
I thought he was gonna hurt us.

32:41.586 --> 32:44.007
Or worse.

32:44.007 --> 32:46.303
‐ It's all right. Go on.

32:48.099 --> 32:50.019
‐ Thank goodness
he didn't stay.

32:50.019 --> 32:52.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:52.190 --> 32:54.946
‐ What do you mean?

32:54.946 --> 32:58.161
‐ A car came
into the parking lot, and‐‐

32:58.161 --> 33:01.041
and your nephew saw it
and he‐‐he left my cabin

33:01.041 --> 33:02.545
and he ran off into the woods.

33:02.545 --> 33:05.926
And then a man got out
of the car

33:05.926 --> 33:08.139
and he started
following your nephew

33:08.139 --> 33:12.022
and I'm‐‐
I'm pretty sure that...

33:12.022 --> 33:14.359
that he had a gun.

33:14.359 --> 33:16.740
‐ What man?

33:16.740 --> 33:18.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:18.451 --> 33:21.498
‐ N‐‐no, I don't‐‐I don't want
to get anybody in trouble.

33:21.498 --> 33:24.421
You know, I‐‐I just‐‐
‐ What man?

33:24.421 --> 33:27.219
‐ [sighs]

33:27.219 --> 33:30.058
I am not a racist, Mr. Merrill,

33:30.058 --> 33:32.354
so I don't want
to cast aspersions

33:32.354 --> 33:36.028
based on, you know,
skin color.

33:36.028 --> 33:38.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:38.324 --> 33:40.829
‐ Was he yea big...

33:40.829 --> 33:43.084
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:43.084 --> 33:45.631
Or yea big?

33:45.631 --> 33:52.645
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:53.981 --> 33:56.402
‐ [exhales sharply]

33:56.402 --> 33:59.617
[sighs, sniffles]

33:59.617 --> 34:01.874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:01.874 --> 34:03.515
ABDI:
[speaking Somali]

34:14.689 --> 34:17.319
[car chirps]

34:17.319 --> 34:20.325
<i>[sinister music]</i>

34:20.325 --> 34:21.953
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:21.953 --> 34:23.623
[gunshots]

34:23.623 --> 34:26.838
[all grunting]

34:26.838 --> 34:30.512
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:30.512 --> 34:32.516
ATTACKER: [grunts]

34:32.516 --> 34:39.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:44.582 --> 34:47.462
POP: This shit makes the office
smell like a skunk's asshole.

34:47.462 --> 34:50.385
‐ What kind of asshole
does your pipe smell like?

34:50.385 --> 34:53.934
‐ George Washington's asshole.
‐ [laughs]

34:53.934 --> 34:57.357
POP: So, the new tea lady
still making trouble?

34:57.357 --> 34:59.027
ABDI: Uh‐uh.

34:59.027 --> 35:01.783
She decided
that being a problem
was too much of a problem.

35:01.783 --> 35:05.164
‐ Mm.
They're very tough people,
but...

35:05.164 --> 35:08.087
but you're good
with the skinnies.

35:08.087 --> 35:10.383
‐ I'm good with everybody, Pop.

35:10.383 --> 35:13.765
POP: The point is, son...

35:13.765 --> 35:15.519
it's gonna be yours.

35:15.519 --> 35:17.230
ABDI: Hmm?

35:17.230 --> 35:19.192
‐ The mall.

35:19.192 --> 35:21.614
Not just collections.
The title.

35:21.614 --> 35:23.535
The whole nut.

35:23.535 --> 35:26.290
Your people, your milk cow.

35:26.290 --> 35:27.960
<i>[mellow music plays on radio]</i>

35:27.960 --> 35:32.135
And there's something else.
Listen...

35:32.135 --> 35:34.974
you and your sister...

35:34.974 --> 35:38.899
you're as much family to me
as the boys.

35:38.899 --> 35:41.738
And I was thinking,
if it's something you want,

35:41.738 --> 35:44.159
we should talk about adoption.

35:44.159 --> 35:46.497
Officially, you know.

35:46.497 --> 35:50.756
Make things easier
down the line.

35:50.756 --> 35:53.385
Of course, if‐‐if you're happy
with the way things are,

35:53.385 --> 35:55.223
you know, you're grown.

35:55.223 --> 35:59.147
So...it's just more
for the business side
of things, you know.

35:59.147 --> 36:01.986
‐ So it's just business?

36:01.986 --> 36:04.742
‐ Always.

36:04.742 --> 36:06.411
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:06.411 --> 36:09.292
So...

36:09.292 --> 36:10.629
deal?

36:10.629 --> 36:12.423
ABDI:
Uh, I have to talk to Nadia,

36:12.423 --> 36:14.512
but I guess
it could be all right.

36:14.512 --> 36:16.808
‐ [chuckling] All right.
All right.

36:16.808 --> 36:18.854
BOTH: Yeah.
POP: That's good news.

36:18.854 --> 36:21.108
<i>[sinister music]</i>

36:21.108 --> 36:23.279
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:23.279 --> 36:26.285
[loud metallic banging]

36:26.285 --> 36:29.374
[approaching footsteps]

36:29.374 --> 36:36.388
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:42.693 --> 36:45.156
‐ You look like shit.

36:51.711 --> 36:54.382
What the fuck do you want, Pop?

36:54.382 --> 36:57.347
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:57.347 --> 36:59.309
‐ What happened to Ace?

36:59.309 --> 37:01.021
Where is he?

37:01.021 --> 37:02.733
‐ Mm.

37:02.733 --> 37:05.530
‐ Fuckin' be coy with me‐‐
where'd you dump the body?

37:05.530 --> 37:09.914
‐ [laughing]

37:09.914 --> 37:12.628
‐ Something funny?
ABDI: [laughing]

37:12.628 --> 37:16.218
Yes. This big show.

37:16.218 --> 37:19.140
Cops. Ooh.

37:19.140 --> 37:22.523
What's all this bullshit,
old man?

37:22.523 --> 37:24.568
You're not gonna hurt me.

37:24.568 --> 37:27.073
You're gonna let me go
right now,

37:27.073 --> 37:31.874
or I'm gonna tell Nadia
the truth about you.

37:31.874 --> 37:34.505
We both know
you can't have that.

37:34.505 --> 37:37.720
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:37.720 --> 37:40.726
[insects chirping]

37:40.726 --> 37:44.525
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:44.525 --> 37:46.486
[keys jingling]

37:46.486 --> 37:49.492
[car alarm wailing]

37:49.492 --> 37:53.877
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:53.877 --> 37:56.883
[multiple car alarms wailing]

37:56.883 --> 38:03.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:06.819 --> 38:10.201
[car alarm chirps,
alarms stop]

38:10.201 --> 38:13.040
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:13.040 --> 38:16.046
[beetles buzzing]

38:16.046 --> 38:23.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:23.018 --> 38:25.397
‐ Who said I did that to Ace?

38:25.397 --> 38:27.653
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:27.653 --> 38:30.282
POP: Eyewitness.
ABDI: "Eyewitness"?

38:30.282 --> 38:31.786
Bullshit.

38:31.786 --> 38:33.205
[chair clatters]

38:33.205 --> 38:36.294
Did they also eyewitness him
firebombing my house?

38:36.294 --> 38:39.425
POP: So you tailed him
to the Stargazer,

38:39.425 --> 38:42.599
then you finally gave him
what he deserved.

38:42.599 --> 38:47.860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:47.860 --> 38:51.241
Tell me where
you put the fucking body.

38:51.241 --> 38:54.122
ABDI: Talk, talk, talk, talk.

38:54.122 --> 38:56.627
You wanna torture someone,
you torture them.

38:56.627 --> 38:59.967
You wanna kill them, kill them.

38:59.967 --> 39:02.890
I thought you already knew that
from the army.

39:02.890 --> 39:05.436
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:05.436 --> 39:08.358
If I had you tied up...

39:08.358 --> 39:11.072
we wouldn't be talking now.

39:11.072 --> 39:12.534
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:12.534 --> 39:15.289
‐ I believe you
about that, Abdi.

39:15.289 --> 39:22.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:23.472 --> 39:26.979
ABDI: You're such
a fucking hypocrite, Pop.

39:26.979 --> 39:30.737
You hope I killed him 'cause
then we'll be even, fair.

39:30.737 --> 39:32.490
Just business.

39:32.490 --> 39:34.745
But we will never be
just business,

39:34.745 --> 39:37.291
and we will never be
a family either.

39:37.291 --> 39:39.672
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:39.672 --> 39:41.801
POP: [grunts]

39:41.801 --> 39:44.430
[chair creaks]

39:44.430 --> 39:51.444
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:57.331 --> 40:00.588
[helicopter whirring]

40:00.588 --> 40:02.551
[indistinct shouting]

40:02.551 --> 40:05.557
[guns shooting,
people shouting]

40:05.557 --> 40:07.393
<i>[gunshot echoes]</i>

40:07.393 --> 40:09.690
[dog growling, barking]

40:09.690 --> 40:13.698
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:13.698 --> 40:15.618
[door opens]

40:15.618 --> 40:17.998
[door slams]

40:17.998 --> 40:20.419
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:20.419 --> 40:23.133
[dog growling]

40:23.133 --> 40:26.724
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:26.724 --> 40:29.563
[dog growling, barking]

40:29.563 --> 40:31.859
POP: Still not a dog lover?

40:31.859 --> 40:33.863
ABDI:
Keep that fucking thing away.

40:33.863 --> 40:36.076
‐ Bobby Orr here has got
a nose for Ace.

40:36.076 --> 40:37.328
Always did.

40:37.328 --> 40:38.790
Let's see what he has to say.

40:38.790 --> 40:40.042
[barking]

40:40.042 --> 40:42.964
ABDI: [whimpers]
What the fuck, Pop?

40:42.964 --> 40:45.427
‐ Where's the fucking body?
ABDI: I don't know!

40:46.555 --> 40:50.062
‐ Where's the fucking body?

